{"dhp44-59":{"dhp44:0.1":{"pli":"Khuddakanikāya ","eng":"Minor Collection ","html":"<section class='range'  id='dhp44-59'><header><ul><li class='division'>{}</li>"},"dhp44:0.2":{"pli":"Dhammapada ","eng":"Sayings of the Dhamma 44–59 ","html":"<li class='subdivision'>{}</li></ul>"},"dhp44:0.3":{"pli":"Pupphavagga ","eng":"4. Flowers ","html":"<h1 class='range-title'>{}</h1></header>"},"dhp44:0.4":{"pli":"Pathavikathāpasutapañcasatabhikkhuvatthu ","html":"<article id='dhp44'><h2 class='sutta-title'>{}</h2>"},"dhp44:1":{"pli":"Ko imaṃ pathaviṃ vicessati, ","eng":"Who bestirs this earth, ","html":"<blockquote class='gatha'><p><span class='verse-line'>{}</span>","comm":"The verbs <i lang='pi' translate='no'>vicessati</i> and <i lang='pi' translate='no'>pacessati</i> in this verse appear to be unique. I take them to be from the Sanskrit <i lang='pi' translate='no'>ceṣṭ</i> (“move, explore”) rather than <i lang='pi' translate='no'>ci</i> (“gather”). They can then be read as present tense, which makes better sense of the verse. Sanskrit and Gandhari parallels have a variety of forms, all of which maintain the distinction between the <i lang='pi' translate='no'>vi</i> and <i lang='pi' translate='no'>pa</i> prefixes. | I take <i lang='pi' translate='no'>vicessati</i> in the sense “stir, agitate”, with reference to such passages as <a href='index.html?q=an7.69#15.1'>AN 7.69:15.1</a>, where the noble one inspires the gods. The commentary, rather, suggests the sense “explore, investigate”. A variant reading <i lang='pi' translate='no'>vijessati</i> yields the sense “shall conquer”. "},"dhp44:2":{"pli":"Yamalokañca imaṃ sadevakaṃ; ","eng":"and the Yama realm with its gods? ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"dhp44:3":{"pli":"Ko dhammapadaṃ sudesitaṃ, ","eng":"Who sets out the well-taught word of truth, ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>","comm":"The verb <i lang='pi' translate='no'>pacessati</i> is exceedingly rare, but the late tantric text Sarvatathāgatādhiṣṭhāna Vyūhasūtra has <i lang='pi' translate='no'>praceṣṭavyaḥ</i>, evidently in the sense of “setting out” scents, flowers, etc. on a shrine. Compare the sense of “having prepared” (the offering for the fire, <i lang='pi' translate='no'>ceṣṭitvā</i>) at Bṛhadāraṇyaka Upaniṣad 6.4.19. "},"dhp44:4":{"pli":"Kusalo pupphamiva pacessati. ","eng":"as an expert a flower? ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span></p></blockquote></article>"},"dhp45:1":{"pli":"Sekho pathaviṃ vicessati, ","eng":"A trainee bestirs this earth, ","html":"<article id='dhp45'><blockquote class='gatha'><p><span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"dhp45:2":{"pli":"Yamalokañca imaṃ sadevakaṃ; ","eng":"and the Yama realm with its gods. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"dhp45:3":{"pli":"Sekho dhammapadaṃ sudesitaṃ, ","eng":"A trainee sets out the well-taught word of truth, ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"dhp45:4":{"pli":"Kusalo pupphamiva pacessati. ","eng":"as an expert a flower. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span></p></blockquote></article>"},"dhp46:0":{"pli":"Marīcikammaṭṭhānikabhikkhuvatthu ","html":"<article id='dhp46'><h2 class='sutta-title'>{}</h2>"},"dhp46:1":{"pli":"Pheṇūpamaṃ kāyamimaṃ viditvā, ","eng":"Knowing this body’s like foam, ","html":"<blockquote class='gatha'><p><span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"dhp46:2":{"pli":"Marīcidhammaṃ abhisambudhāno; ","eng":"realizing it’s all just a mirage, ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"dhp46:3":{"pli":"Chetvāna mārassa papupphakāni, ","eng":"and cutting off Māra’s blossoming, ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"dhp46:4":{"pli":"Adassanaṃ maccurājassa gacche. ","eng":"vanish from the King of Death. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span></p></blockquote></article>"},"dhp47:0":{"pli":"Viṭaṭūbhavatthu ","html":"<article id='dhp47'><h2 class='sutta-title'>{}</h2>"},"dhp47:1":{"pli":"Pupphāni heva pacinantaṃ, ","eng":"As a mighty flood sweeps off a sleeping village, ","html":"<blockquote class='gatha'><p><span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"dhp47:2":{"pli":"byāsattamanasaṃ naraṃ; ","eng":"death steals away a man ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"dhp47:3":{"pli":"Suttaṃ gāmaṃ mahoghova, ","eng":"even as he gathers flowers, ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"dhp47:4":{"pli":"maccu ādāya gacchati. ","eng":"his mind caught up in them. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span></p></blockquote></article>"},"dhp48:0":{"pli":"Patipūjikakumārivatthu ","html":"<article id='dhp48'><h2 class='sutta-title'>{}</h2>"},"dhp48:1":{"pli":"Pupphāni heva pacinantaṃ, ","eng":"The terminator gains control of the man ","html":"<blockquote class='gatha'><p><span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"dhp48:2":{"pli":"byāsattamanasaṃ naraṃ; ","eng":"who has not had his fill of pleasures, ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"dhp48:3":{"pli":"Atittaññeva kāmesu, ","eng":"even as he gathers flowers, ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"dhp48:4":{"pli":"antako kurute vasaṃ. ","eng":"his mind caught up in them. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span></p></blockquote></article>"},"dhp49:0":{"pli":"Macchariyakosiyaseṭṭhivatthu ","html":"<article id='dhp49'><h2 class='sutta-title'>{}</h2>"},"dhp49:1":{"pli":"Yathāpi bhamaro pupphaṃ, ","eng":"A bee takes the nectar ","html":"<blockquote class='gatha'><p><span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"dhp49:2":{"pli":"vaṇṇagandhamaheṭhayaṃ; ","eng":"and moves on, doing no damage ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"dhp49:3":{"pli":"Paleti rasamādāya, ","eng":"to the flower’s beauty and fragrance; ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"dhp49:4":{"pli":"evaṃ gāme munī care. ","eng":"and that’s how a sage should walk in the village. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span></p></blockquote></article>"},"dhp50:0":{"pli":"Pāveyyaājīvakavatthu ","html":"<article id='dhp50'><h2 class='sutta-title'>{}</h2>"},"dhp50:1":{"pli":"Na paresaṃ vilomāni, ","eng":"Don’t find fault with others, ","html":"<blockquote class='gatha'><p><span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"dhp50:2":{"pli":"na paresaṃ katākataṃ; ","eng":"with what they’ve done or left undone. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"dhp50:3":{"pli":"Attanova avekkheyya, ","eng":"You should only watch yourself, ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"dhp50:4":{"pli":"katāni akatāni ca. ","eng":"what you’ve done or left undone. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span></p></blockquote></article>"},"dhp51:0":{"pli":"Chattapāṇiupāsakavatthu ","html":"<article id='dhp51'><h2 class='sutta-title'>{}</h2>"},"dhp51:1":{"pli":"Yathāpi ruciraṃ pupphaṃ, ","eng":"Just like a glorious flower ","html":"<blockquote class='gatha'><p><span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"dhp51:2":{"pli":"vaṇṇavantaṃ agandhakaṃ; ","eng":"that’s colorful but lacks fragrance; ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"dhp51:3":{"pli":"Evaṃ subhāsitā vācā, ","eng":"eloquent speech is fruitless ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"dhp51:4":{"pli":"aphalā hoti akubbato. ","eng":"for one who does not act on it. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span></p></blockquote></article>"},"dhp52:1":{"pli":"Yathāpi ruciraṃ pupphaṃ, ","eng":"Just like a glorious flower ","html":"<article id='dhp52'><blockquote class='gatha'><p><span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"dhp52:2":{"pli":"Vaṇṇavantaṃ sagandhakaṃ; ","eng":"that’s both colorful and fragrant, ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"dhp52:3":{"pli":"Evaṃ subhāsitā vācā, ","eng":"eloquent speech is fruitful ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"dhp52:4":{"pli":"Saphalā hoti kubbato. ","eng":"for one who acts on it. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span></p></blockquote></article>"},"dhp53:0":{"pli":"Visākhāvatthu ","html":"<article id='dhp53'><h2 class='sutta-title'>{}</h2>"},"dhp53:1":{"pli":"Yathāpi puppharāsimhā, ","eng":"Just as one would create many garlands ","html":"<blockquote class='gatha'><p><span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"dhp53:2":{"pli":"kayirā mālāguṇe bahū; ","eng":"from a heap of flowers, ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"dhp53:3":{"pli":"Evaṃ jātena maccena, ","eng":"when a person has come to be born, ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"dhp53:4":{"pli":"kattabbaṃ kusalaṃ bahuṃ. ","eng":"they should do many skillful things. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span></p></blockquote></article>"},"dhp54:0":{"pli":"Ānandattherapañhavatthu ","html":"<article id='dhp54'><h2 class='sutta-title'>{}</h2>"},"dhp54:1":{"pli":"Na pupphagandho paṭivātameti, ","eng":"The fragrance of flowers doesn’t spread upwind, ","html":"<blockquote class='gatha'><p><span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"dhp54:2":{"pli":"Na candanaṃ tagaramallikā vā; ","eng":"nor sandalwood, pinwheel, or jasmine; ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"dhp54:3":{"pli":"Satañca gandho paṭivātameti, ","eng":"but the fragrance of the good spreads upwind; ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"dhp54:4":{"pli":"Sabbā disā sappuriso pavāyati. ","eng":"a true person’s virtue spreads in every direction. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span></p></blockquote></article>"},"dhp55:1":{"pli":"Candanaṃ tagaraṃ vāpi, ","eng":"Among all the fragrances—","html":"<article id='dhp55'><blockquote class='gatha'><p><span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"dhp55:2":{"pli":"uppalaṃ atha vassikī; ","eng":"sandalwood or pinwheel ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"dhp55:3":{"pli":"Etesaṃ gandhajātānaṃ, ","eng":"or lotus or jasmine—","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"dhp55:4":{"pli":"sīlagandho anuttaro. ","eng":"the fragrance of virtue is supreme. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span></p></blockquote></article>"},"dhp56:0":{"pli":"Mahākassapattherapiṇḍapātadinnavatthu ","html":"<article id='dhp56'><h2 class='sutta-title'>{}</h2>"},"dhp56:1":{"pli":"Appamatto ayaṃ gandho, ","eng":"Faint is the fragrance ","html":"<blockquote class='gatha'><p><span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"dhp56:2":{"pli":"yāyaṃ tagaracandanī; ","eng":"of sandal or pinwheel; ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"dhp56:3":{"pli":"Yo ca sīlavataṃ gandho, ","eng":"but the fragrance of the virtuous ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"dhp56:4":{"pli":"vāti devesu uttamo. ","eng":"floats to the highest gods. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span></p></blockquote></article>"},"dhp57:0":{"pli":"Godhikattheraparinibbānavatthu ","html":"<article id='dhp57'><h2 class='sutta-title'>{}</h2>"},"dhp57:1":{"pli":"Tesaṃ sampannasīlānaṃ, ","eng":"For those accomplished in ethics, ","html":"<blockquote class='gatha'><p><span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"dhp57:2":{"pli":"appamādavihārinaṃ; ","eng":"meditating diligently, ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"dhp57:3":{"pli":"Sammadaññāvimuttānaṃ, ","eng":"freed through the highest knowledge, ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"dhp57:4":{"pli":"māro maggaṃ na vindati. ","eng":"Māra cannot find their path. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span></p></blockquote></article>"},"dhp58:0":{"pli":"Garahadinnavatthu ","html":"<article id='dhp58'><h2 class='sutta-title'>{}</h2>"},"dhp58:1":{"pli":"Yathā saṅkāradhānasmiṃ, ","eng":"From a heap of trash ","html":"<blockquote class='gatha'><p><span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"dhp58:2":{"pli":"ujjhitasmiṃ mahāpathe; ","eng":"discarded on the highway, ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"dhp58:3":{"pli":"Padumaṃ tattha jāyetha, ","eng":"a lotus might blossom, ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"dhp58:4":{"pli":"sucigandhaṃ manoramaṃ. ","eng":"fragrant and delightful. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span></p></blockquote></article>"},"dhp59:1":{"pli":"Evaṃ saṅkārabhūtesu, ","eng":"So too, among those thought of as trash, ","html":"<article id='dhp59'><blockquote class='gatha'><p><span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"dhp59:2":{"pli":"andhabhūte puthujjane; ","eng":"a disciple of the perfect Buddha ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"dhp59:3":{"pli":"Atirocati paññāya, ","eng":"outshines with their wisdom ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"dhp59:4":{"pli":"sammāsambuddhasāvako. ","eng":"the blind ordinary folk. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span></p></blockquote>"},"dhp59:5":{"pli":"Pupphavaggo catuttho. ","html":"<p class='endvagga'>{}</p></article></section>"}},"dhp60-75":{"dhp60:0.1":{"pli":"Khuddakanikāya ","eng":"Minor Collection ","html":"<section class='range'  id='dhp60-75'><header><ul><li class='division'>{}</li>"},"dhp60:0.2":{"pli":"Dhammapada ","eng":"Sayings of the Dhamma 60–75 ","html":"<li class='subdivision'>{}</li></ul>"},"dhp60:0.3":{"pli":"Bālavagga ","eng":"5. The Fool ","html":"<h1 class='range-title'>{}</h1></header>"},"dhp60:0.4":{"pli":"Aññatarapurisavatthu ","html":"<article id='dhp60'><h2 class='sutta-title'>{}</h2>"},"dhp60:1":{"pli":"Dīghā jāgarato ratti, ","eng":"Long is the night for the wakeful; ","html":"<blockquote class='gatha'><p><span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"dhp60:2":{"pli":"dīghaṃ santassa yojanaṃ; ","eng":"long is the league for the weary; ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"dhp60:3":{"pli":"Dīgho bālāna saṃsāro, ","eng":"long transmigrate the fools ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"dhp60:4":{"pli":"saddhammaṃ avijānataṃ. ","eng":"who don’t understand the true teaching. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span></p></blockquote></article>"},"dhp61:0":{"pli":"Mahākassapasaddhivihārikavatthu ","html":"<article id='dhp61'><h2 class='sutta-title'>{}</h2>"},"dhp61:1":{"pli":"Carañce nādhigaccheyya, ","eng":"If while wandering you find no partner ","html":"<blockquote class='gatha'><p><span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"dhp61:2":{"pli":"Seyyaṃ sadisamattano; ","eng":"equal or better than yourself, ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"dhp61:3":{"pli":"Ekacariyaṃ daḷhaṃ kayirā, ","eng":"then firmly resolve to wander alone—","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"dhp61:4":{"pli":"Natthi bāle sahāyatā. ","eng":"there’s no fellowship with fools. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span></p></blockquote></article>"},"dhp62:0":{"pli":"Ānandaseṭṭhivatthu ","html":"<article id='dhp62'><h2 class='sutta-title'>{}</h2>"},"dhp62:1":{"pli":"Puttā matthi dhanaṃ matthi, ","eng":"“Sons are mine, wealth is mine”—","html":"<blockquote class='gatha'><p><span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"dhp62:2":{"pli":"iti bālo vihaññati; ","eng":"thus the fool frets. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"dhp62:3":{"pli":"Attā hi attano natthi, ","eng":"For even your self is not your own, ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"dhp62:4":{"pli":"kuto puttā kuto dhanaṃ. ","eng":"let alone your sons or wealth. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span></p></blockquote></article>"},"dhp63:0":{"pli":"Gaṇṭhibhedakacoravatthu ","html":"<article id='dhp63'><h2 class='sutta-title'>{}</h2>"},"dhp63:1":{"pli":"Yo bālo maññati bālyaṃ, ","eng":"The fool who thinks they’re a fool ","html":"<blockquote class='gatha'><p><span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"dhp63:2":{"pli":"paṇḍito vāpi tena so; ","eng":"is wise at least to that extent. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"dhp63:3":{"pli":"Bālo ca paṇḍitamānī, ","eng":"But the true fool is said to be one ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"dhp63:4":{"pli":"sa ve “bālo”ti vuccati. ","eng":"who imagines that they are wise. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span></p></blockquote></article>"},"dhp64:0":{"pli":"Udāyittheravatthu ","html":"<article id='dhp64'><h2 class='sutta-title'>{}</h2>"},"dhp64:1":{"pli":"Yāvajīvampi ce bālo, ","eng":"Though a fool attends to the wise ","html":"<blockquote class='gatha'><p><span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"dhp64:2":{"pli":"paṇḍitaṃ payirupāsati; ","eng":"even for the rest of their life, ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"dhp64:3":{"pli":"Na so dhammaṃ vijānāti, ","eng":"they still don’t understand the teaching, ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"dhp64:4":{"pli":"dabbī sūparasaṃ yathā. ","eng":"like a spoon the taste of the soup. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span></p></blockquote></article>"},"dhp65:0":{"pli":"Tiṃsapāveyyakabhikkhuvatthu ","html":"<article id='dhp65'><h2 class='sutta-title'>{}</h2>"},"dhp65:1":{"pli":"Muhuttamapi ce viññū, ","eng":"If a clever person attends to the wise ","html":"<blockquote class='gatha'><p><span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"dhp65:2":{"pli":"paṇḍitaṃ payirupāsati; ","eng":"even just for an hour or so, ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"dhp65:3":{"pli":"Khippaṃ dhammaṃ vijānāti, ","eng":"they swiftly understand the teaching, ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"dhp65:4":{"pli":"jivhā sūparasaṃ yathā. ","eng":"like a tongue the taste of the soup. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span></p></blockquote></article>"},"dhp66:0":{"pli":"Suppabuddhakuṭṭhivatthu ","html":"<article id='dhp66'><h2 class='sutta-title'>{}</h2>"},"dhp66:1":{"pli":"Caranti bālā dummedhā, ","eng":"Fools and simpletons behave ","html":"<blockquote class='gatha'><p><span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"dhp66:2":{"pli":"amitteneva attanā; ","eng":"like their own worst enemies, ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"dhp66:3":{"pli":"Karontā pāpakaṃ kammaṃ, ","eng":"doing wicked deeds ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"dhp66:4":{"pli":"yaṃ hoti kaṭukapphalaṃ. ","eng":"that ripen as bitter fruit. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span></p></blockquote></article>"},"dhp67:0":{"pli":"Kassakavatthu ","html":"<article id='dhp67'><h2 class='sutta-title'>{}</h2>"},"dhp67:1":{"pli":"Na taṃ kammaṃ kataṃ sādhu, ","eng":"It’s not good to do a deed ","html":"<blockquote class='gatha'><p><span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"dhp67:2":{"pli":"yaṃ katvā anutappati; ","eng":"that plagues you later on, ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"dhp67:3":{"pli":"Yassa assumukho rodaṃ, ","eng":"for which you weep and wail, ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"dhp67:4":{"pli":"vipākaṃ paṭisevati. ","eng":"as its effect stays with you. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span></p></blockquote></article>"},"dhp68:0":{"pli":"Sumanamālākāravatthu ","html":"<article id='dhp68'><h2 class='sutta-title'>{}</h2>"},"dhp68:1":{"pli":"Tañca kammaṃ kataṃ sādhu, ","eng":"It is good to do a deed ","html":"<blockquote class='gatha'><p><span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"dhp68:2":{"pli":"yaṃ katvā nānutappati; ","eng":"that doesn’t plague you later on, ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"dhp68:3":{"pli":"Yassa patīto sumano, ","eng":"that gladdens and cheers, ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"dhp68:4":{"pli":"vipākaṃ paṭisevati. ","eng":"as its effect stays with you. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span></p></blockquote></article>"},"dhp69:0":{"pli":"Uppalavaṇṇattherīvatthu ","html":"<article id='dhp69'><h2 class='sutta-title'>{}</h2>"},"dhp69:1":{"pli":"Madhuṃvā maññati bālo, ","eng":"The fool imagines that evil is sweet, ","html":"<blockquote class='gatha'><p><span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"dhp69:2":{"pli":"yāva pāpaṃ na paccati; ","eng":"so long as it has not yet ripened. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"dhp69:3":{"pli":"Yadā ca paccati pāpaṃ, ","eng":"But as soon as that evil ripens, ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"dhp69:4":{"pli":"atha dukkhaṃ nigacchati. ","eng":"they fall into suffering. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span></p></blockquote></article>"},"dhp70:0":{"pli":"Jambukattheravatthu ","html":"<article id='dhp70'><h2 class='sutta-title'>{}</h2>"},"dhp70:1":{"pli":"Māse māse kusaggena, ","eng":"Month after month a fool may eat ","html":"<blockquote class='gatha'><p><span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"dhp70:2":{"pli":"bālo bhuñjeyya bhojanaṃ; ","eng":"food from a grass-blade’s tip; ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"dhp70:3":{"pli":"Na so saṅkhātadhammānaṃ, ","eng":"but they’ll never be worth a sixteenth part ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"dhp70:4":{"pli":"kalaṃ agghati soḷasiṃ. ","eng":"of one who has appraised the teaching. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span></p></blockquote></article>"},"dhp71:0":{"pli":"Ahipetavatthu ","html":"<article id='dhp71'><h2 class='sutta-title'>{}</h2>"},"dhp71:1":{"pli":"Na hi pāpaṃ kataṃ kammaṃ, ","eng":"For a wicked deed that has been done ","html":"<blockquote class='gatha'><p><span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"dhp71:2":{"pli":"Sajjukhīraṃva muccati; ","eng":"does not curdle quickly like milk. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"dhp71:3":{"pli":"Ḍahantaṃ bālamanveti, ","eng":"Smoldering, it follows the fool, ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"dhp71:4":{"pli":"Bhasmacchannova pāvako. ","eng":"like a fire smothered over with ash. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span></p></blockquote></article>"},"dhp72:0":{"pli":"Saṭṭhikūṭapetavatthu ","html":"<article id='dhp72'><h2 class='sutta-title'>{}</h2>"},"dhp72:1":{"pli":"Yāvadeva anatthāya, ","eng":"Whatever fame a fool may get, ","html":"<blockquote class='gatha'><p><span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"dhp72:2":{"pli":"ñattaṃ bālassa jāyati; ","eng":"it only gives rise to harm. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"dhp72:3":{"pli":"Hanti bālassa sukkaṃsaṃ, ","eng":"Whatever good features they have it ruins, ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"dhp72:4":{"pli":"muddhamassa vipātayaṃ. ","eng":"and blows their head into bits. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span></p></blockquote></article>"},"dhp73:0":{"pli":"Cittagahapativatthu ","html":"<article id='dhp73'><h2 class='sutta-title'>{}</h2>"},"dhp73:1":{"pli":"Asantaṃ bhāvanamiccheyya, ","eng":"They’d seek the esteem that they lack, ","html":"<blockquote class='gatha'><p><span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"dhp73:2":{"pli":"Purekkhārañca bhikkhusu; ","eng":"and status among the mendicants; ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"dhp73:3":{"pli":"Āvāsesu ca issariyaṃ, ","eng":"authority over monasteries, ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"dhp73:4":{"pli":"Pūjaṃ parakulesu ca. ","eng":"and honor among other families. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span></p></blockquote></article>"},"dhp74:1":{"pli":"Mameva kata maññantu, ","eng":"“Let both layfolk and renunciants think ","html":"<article id='dhp74'><blockquote class='gatha'><p><span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"dhp74:2":{"pli":"gihī pabbajitā ubho; ","eng":"the work was done by me alone. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"dhp74:3":{"pli":"Mamevātivasā assu, ","eng":"In anything at all that’s to be done, ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"dhp74:4":{"pli":"kiccākiccesu kismici; ","eng":"let them fall under my sway alone.” ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"dhp74:5":{"pli":"Iti bālassa saṅkappo, ","eng":"So thinks the fool, ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"dhp74:6":{"pli":"icchā māno ca vaḍḍhati. ","eng":"their greed and pride only growing. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span></p></blockquote></article>"},"dhp75:0":{"pli":"Vanavāsitissasāmaṇeravatthu ","html":"<article id='dhp75'><h2 class='sutta-title'>{}</h2>"},"dhp75:1":{"pli":"Aññā hi lābhūpanisā, ","eng":"For the means to profit and the path to quenching ","html":"<blockquote class='gatha'><p><span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"dhp75:2":{"pli":"aññā nibbānagāminī; ","eng":"are two quite different things. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"dhp75:3":{"pli":"Evametaṃ abhiññāya, ","eng":"A mendicant disciple of the Buddha, ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"dhp75:4":{"pli":"bhikkhu buddhassa sāvako; ","eng":"understanding what this really means, ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"dhp75:5":{"pli":"Sakkāraṃ nābhinandeyya, ","eng":"would never delight in honors, ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"dhp75:6":{"pli":"vivekamanubrūhaye. ","eng":"but rather would foster seclusion. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span></p></blockquote>"},"dhp75:7":{"pli":"Bālavaggo pañcamo. ","html":"<p class='endvagga'>{}</p></article></section>"}},"dhp76-89":{"dhp76:0.1":{"pli":"Khuddakanikāya ","eng":"Minor Collection ","html":"<section class='range'  id='dhp76-89'><header><ul><li class='division'>{}</li>"},"dhp76:0.2":{"pli":"Dhammapada ","eng":"Sayings of the Dhamma 76–89 ","html":"<li class='subdivision'>{}</li></ul>"},"dhp76:0.3":{"pli":"Paṇḍitavagga ","eng":"6. The Astute ","html":"<h1 class='range-title'>{}</h1></header>"},"dhp76:0.4":{"pli":"Rādhattheravatthu ","html":"<article id='dhp76'><h2 class='sutta-title'>{}</h2>"},"dhp76:1":{"pli":"Nidhīnaṃva pavattāraṃ, ","eng":"Regard one who sees your faults ","html":"<blockquote class='gatha'><p><span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"dhp76:2":{"pli":"yaṃ passe vajjadassinaṃ; ","eng":"as a guide to a hidden treasure. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"dhp76:3":{"pli":"Niggayhavādiṃ medhāviṃ, ","eng":"Stay close to one so wise and astute ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"dhp76:4":{"pli":"tādisaṃ paṇḍitaṃ bhaje; ","eng":"who corrects you when you need it. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"dhp76:5":{"pli":"Tādisaṃ bhajamānassa, ","eng":"Sticking close to such an impartial person, ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"dhp76:6":{"pli":"seyyo hoti na pāpiyo. ","eng":"things get better, not worse. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span></p></blockquote></article>"},"dhp77:0":{"pli":"Assajipunabbasukavatthu ","html":"<article id='dhp77'><h2 class='sutta-title'>{}</h2>"},"dhp77:1":{"pli":"Ovadeyyānusāseyya, ","eng":"Advise and instruct; ","html":"<blockquote class='gatha'><p><span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"dhp77:2":{"pli":"asabbhā ca nivāraye; ","eng":"curb wickedness: ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"dhp77:3":{"pli":"Satañhi so piyo hoti, ","eng":"for you shall be loved by the good, ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"dhp77:4":{"pli":"asataṃ hoti appiyo. ","eng":"and disliked by the bad. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span></p></blockquote></article>"},"dhp78:0":{"pli":"Channattheravatthu ","html":"<article id='dhp78'><h2 class='sutta-title'>{}</h2>"},"dhp78:1":{"pli":"Na bhaje pāpake mitte, ","eng":"Don’t mix with bad friends, ","html":"<blockquote class='gatha'><p><span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"dhp78:2":{"pli":"na bhaje purisādhame; ","eng":"nor with the worst of men. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"dhp78:3":{"pli":"Bhajetha mitte kalyāṇe, ","eng":"Mix with spiritual friends, ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"dhp78:4":{"pli":"bhajetha purisuttame. ","eng":"and with the best of men. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span></p></blockquote></article>"},"dhp79:0":{"pli":"Mahākappinattheravatthu ","html":"<article id='dhp79'><h2 class='sutta-title'>{}</h2>"},"dhp79:1":{"pli":"Dhammapīti sukhaṃ seti, ","eng":"Through joy in the teaching you sleep at ease, ","html":"<blockquote class='gatha'><p><span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"dhp79:2":{"pli":"vippasannena cetasā; ","eng":"with clear and confident heart. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"dhp79:3":{"pli":"Ariyappavedite dhamme, ","eng":"An astute person always delights in the teaching ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"dhp79:4":{"pli":"sadā ramati paṇḍito. ","eng":"proclaimed by the Noble One. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span></p></blockquote></article>"},"dhp80:0":{"pli":"Paṇḍitasāmaṇeravatthu ","html":"<article id='dhp80'><h2 class='sutta-title'>{}</h2>"},"dhp80:1":{"pli":"Udakañhi nayanti nettikā, ","eng":"Irrigators guide water, ","html":"<blockquote class='gatha'><p><span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"dhp80:2":{"pli":"Usukārā namayanti tejanaṃ; ","eng":"fletchers straighten arrows, ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"dhp80:3":{"pli":"Dāruṃ namayanti tacchakā, ","eng":"carpenters carve timber, ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"dhp80:4":{"pli":"Attānaṃ damayanti paṇḍitā. ","eng":"the astute tame themselves. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span></p></blockquote></article>"},"dhp81:0":{"pli":"Lakuṇḍakabhaddiyattheravatthu ","html":"<article id='dhp81'><h2 class='sutta-title'>{}</h2>"},"dhp81:1":{"pli":"Selo yathā ekaghano, ","eng":"As the wind cannot stir ","html":"<blockquote class='gatha'><p><span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"dhp81:2":{"pli":"vātena na samīrati; ","eng":"a solid mass of rock, ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"dhp81:3":{"pli":"Evaṃ nindāpasaṃsāsu, ","eng":"so too blame and praise ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"dhp81:4":{"pli":"na samiñjanti paṇḍitā. ","eng":"do not affect the wise. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span></p></blockquote></article>"},"dhp82:0":{"pli":"Kāṇamātāvatthu ","html":"<article id='dhp82'><h2 class='sutta-title'>{}</h2>"},"dhp82:1":{"pli":"Yathāpi rahado gambhīro, ","eng":"Like a deep lake, ","html":"<blockquote class='gatha'><p><span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"dhp82:2":{"pli":"vippasanno anāvilo; ","eng":"clear and unclouded, ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"dhp82:3":{"pli":"Evaṃ dhammāni sutvāna, ","eng":"so clear are the astute ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"dhp82:4":{"pli":"vippasīdanti paṇḍitā. ","eng":"when they hear the teachings. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span></p></blockquote></article>"},"dhp83:0":{"pli":"Pañcasatabhikkhuvatthu ","html":"<article id='dhp83'><h2 class='sutta-title'>{}</h2>"},"dhp83:1":{"pli":"Sabbattha ve sappurisā cajanti, ","eng":"True persons give up everything, ","html":"<blockquote class='gatha'><p><span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"dhp83:2":{"pli":"Na kāmakāmā lapayanti santo; ","eng":"they don’t cajole for the things they desire. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"dhp83:3":{"pli":"Sukhena phuṭṭhā atha vā dukhena, ","eng":"Though touched by sadness or happiness, ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"dhp83:4":{"pli":"Na uccāvacaṃ paṇḍitā dassayanti. ","eng":"the astute appear neither depressed nor elated. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span></p></blockquote></article>"},"dhp84:0":{"pli":"Dhammikattheravatthu ","html":"<article id='dhp84'><h2 class='sutta-title'>{}</h2>"},"dhp84:1":{"pli":"Na attahetu na parassa hetu, ","eng":"Never wish for success by unjust means, ","html":"<blockquote class='gatha'><p><span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"dhp84:2":{"pli":"Na puttamicche na dhanaṃ na raṭṭhaṃ; ","eng":"for your own sake or that of another, ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"dhp84:3":{"pli":"Na iccheyya adhammena samiddhimattano, ","eng":"desiring children, wealth, or nation; ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"dhp84:4":{"pli":"Sa sīlavā paññavā dhammiko siyā. ","eng":"rather, be virtuous, wise, and just. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span></p></blockquote></article>"},"dhp85:0":{"pli":"Dhammassavanattheravatthu ","html":"<article id='dhp85'><h2 class='sutta-title'>{}</h2>"},"dhp85:1":{"pli":"Appakā te manussesu, ","eng":"Few are those among humans ","html":"<blockquote class='gatha'><p><span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"dhp85:2":{"pli":"ye janā pāragāmino; ","eng":"who cross to the far shore. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"dhp85:3":{"pli":"Athāyaṃ itarā pajā, ","eng":"The rest just run around ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"dhp85:4":{"pli":"tīramevānudhāvati. ","eng":"on the near shore. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span></p></blockquote></article>"},"dhp86:1":{"pli":"Ye ca kho sammadakkhāte, ","eng":"When the teaching is well explained, ","html":"<article id='dhp86'><blockquote class='gatha'><p><span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"dhp86:2":{"pli":"dhamme dhammānuvattino; ","eng":"those who practice accordingly ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"dhp86:3":{"pli":"Te janā pāramessanti, ","eng":"will cross over ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"dhp86:4":{"pli":"maccudheyyaṃ suduttaraṃ. ","eng":"Death’s dominion so hard to pass. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span></p></blockquote></article>"},"dhp87:0":{"pli":"Pañcasataāgantukabhikkhuvatthu ","html":"<article id='dhp87'><h2 class='sutta-title'>{}</h2>"},"dhp87:1":{"pli":"Kaṇhaṃ dhammaṃ vippahāya, ","eng":"Rid of dark qualities, ","html":"<blockquote class='gatha'><p><span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"dhp87:2":{"pli":"Sukkaṃ bhāvetha paṇḍito; ","eng":"an astute person should develop the bright. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"dhp87:3":{"pli":"Okā anokamāgamma, ","eng":"Leaving home behind ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"dhp87:4":{"pli":"Viveke yattha dūramaṃ. ","eng":"for the seclusion so hard to enjoy, ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span></p></blockquote></article>"},"dhp88:1":{"pli":"Tatrābhiratimiccheyya, ","eng":"try to find satisfaction there, ","html":"<article id='dhp88'><blockquote class='gatha'><p><span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"dhp88:2":{"pli":"hitvā kāme akiñcano; ","eng":"having left behind sensual pleasures. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"dhp88:3":{"pli":"Pariyodapeyya attānaṃ, ","eng":"Owning nothing, an astute person ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"dhp88:4":{"pli":"cittaklesehi paṇḍito. ","eng":"would cleanse themselves of mental corruptions. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span></p></blockquote></article>"},"dhp89:1":{"pli":"Yesaṃ sambodhiyaṅgesu, ","eng":"Those whose minds are rightly developed ","html":"<article id='dhp89'><blockquote class='gatha'><p><span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"dhp89:2":{"pli":"sammā cittaṃ subhāvitaṃ; ","eng":"in the awakening factors; ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"dhp89:3":{"pli":"Ādānapaṭinissagge, ","eng":"who, letting go of attachments, ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"dhp89:4":{"pli":"anupādāya ye ratā; ","eng":"delight in not grasping: ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"dhp89:5":{"pli":"Khīṇāsavā jutimanto, ","eng":"with defilements ended, brilliant, ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"dhp89:6":{"pli":"te loke parinibbutā. ","eng":"they are quenched in this world. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span></p></blockquote>"},"dhp89:7":{"pli":"Paṇḍitavaggo chaṭṭho. ","html":"<p class='endvagga'>{}</p></article></section>"}},"dhp90-99":{"dhp90:0.1":{"pli":"Khuddakanikāya ","eng":"Minor Collection ","html":"<section class='range'  id='dhp90-99'><header><ul><li class='division'>{}</li>"},"dhp90:0.2":{"pli":"Dhammapada ","eng":"Sayings of the Dhamma 90–99 ","html":"<li class='subdivision'>{}</li></ul>"},"dhp90:0.3":{"pli":"Arahantavagga ","eng":"7. The Perfected Ones ","html":"<h1 class='range-title'>{}</h1></header>"},"dhp90:0.4":{"pli":"Jīvakapañhavatthu ","html":"<article id='dhp90'><h2 class='sutta-title'>{}</h2>"},"dhp90:1":{"pli":"Gataddhino visokassa, ","eng":"At journey’s end, rid of sorrow; ","html":"<blockquote class='gatha'><p><span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"dhp90:2":{"pli":"vippamuttassa sabbadhi; ","eng":"everywhere free, ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"dhp90:3":{"pli":"Sabbaganthappahīnassa, ","eng":"all ties given up, ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"dhp90:4":{"pli":"pariḷāho na vijjati. ","eng":"no fever is found in them. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span></p></blockquote></article>"},"dhp91:0":{"pli":"Mahākassapattheravatthu ","html":"<article id='dhp91'><h2 class='sutta-title'>{}</h2>"},"dhp91:1":{"pli":"Uyyuñjanti satīmanto, ","eng":"The mindful apply themselves; ","html":"<blockquote class='gatha'><p><span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"dhp91:2":{"pli":"na nikete ramanti te; ","eng":"they delight in no abode. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"dhp91:3":{"pli":"Haṃsāva pallalaṃ hitvā, ","eng":"Like a swan gone from the marsh, ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"dhp91:4":{"pli":"okamokaṃ jahanti te. ","eng":"they leave home after home behind. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span></p></blockquote></article>"},"dhp92:0":{"pli":"Belaṭṭhasīsattheravatthu ","html":"<article id='dhp92'><h2 class='sutta-title'>{}</h2>"},"dhp92:1":{"pli":"Yesaṃ sannicayo natthi, ","eng":"Those with nothing stored up, ","html":"<blockquote class='gatha'><p><span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"dhp92:2":{"pli":"ye pariññātabhojanā; ","eng":"who have understood their food, ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"dhp92:3":{"pli":"Suññato animitto ca, ","eng":"whose domain is the liberation ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"dhp92:4":{"pli":"vimokkho yesaṃ gocaro; ","eng":"of the signless and the empty: ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"dhp92:5":{"pli":"Ākāseva sakuntānaṃ, ","eng":"their path is hard to trace, ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"dhp92:6":{"pli":"gati tesaṃ durannayā. ","eng":"like birds in the sky. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span></p></blockquote></article>"},"dhp93:0":{"pli":"Anuruddhattheravatthu ","html":"<article id='dhp93'><h2 class='sutta-title'>{}</h2>"},"dhp93:1":{"pli":"Yassāsavā parikkhīṇā, ","eng":"One whose defilements have ended; ","html":"<blockquote class='gatha'><p><span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"dhp93:2":{"pli":"āhāre ca anissito; ","eng":"who’s not attached to food; ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"dhp93:3":{"pli":"Suññato animitto ca, ","eng":"whose domain is the liberation ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"dhp93:4":{"pli":"vimokkho yassa gocaro; ","eng":"of the signless and the empty: ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"dhp93:5":{"pli":"Ākāseva sakuntānaṃ, ","eng":"their track is hard to trace, ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"dhp93:6":{"pli":"padaṃ tassa durannayaṃ. ","eng":"like birds in the sky. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span></p></blockquote></article>"},"dhp94:0":{"pli":"Mahākaccāyanattheravatthu ","html":"<article id='dhp94'><h2 class='sutta-title'>{}</h2>"},"dhp94:1":{"pli":"Yassindriyāni samathaṅgatāni, ","eng":"Whose faculties have become serene, ","html":"<blockquote class='gatha'><p><span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"dhp94:2":{"pli":"Assā yathā sārathinā sudantā; ","eng":"like horses tamed by a charioteer, ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"dhp94:3":{"pli":"Pahīnamānassa anāsavassa, ","eng":"who has abandoned conceit and defilements; ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"dhp94:4":{"pli":"Devāpi tassa pihayanti tādino. ","eng":"the unaffected one is envied by even the gods. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span></p></blockquote></article>"},"dhp95:0":{"pli":"Sāriputtattheravatthu ","html":"<article id='dhp95'><h2 class='sutta-title'>{}</h2>"},"dhp95:1":{"pli":"Pathavisamo no virujjhati, ","eng":"Undisturbed like the earth, ","html":"<blockquote class='gatha'><p><span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"dhp95:2":{"pli":"Indakhilupamo tādi subbato; ","eng":"true to their vows, steady as Indra’s pillar, ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"dhp95:3":{"pli":"Rahadova apetakaddamo, ","eng":"like a lake clear of mud; ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"dhp95:4":{"pli":"Saṃsārā na bhavanti tādino. ","eng":"such a one does not transmigrate. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span></p></blockquote></article>"},"dhp96:0":{"pli":"Kosambivāsitissattherasāmaṇeravatthu ","html":"<article id='dhp96'><h2 class='sutta-title'>{}</h2>"},"dhp96:1":{"pli":"Santaṃ tassa manaṃ hoti, ","eng":"Their mind is peaceful, ","html":"<blockquote class='gatha'><p><span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"dhp96:2":{"pli":"santā vācā ca kamma ca; ","eng":"peaceful are their speech and deeds. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"dhp96:3":{"pli":"Sammadaññāvimuttassa, ","eng":"Such a one is at peace, ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"dhp96:4":{"pli":"upasantassa tādino. ","eng":"rightly freed through enlightenment. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span></p></blockquote></article>"},"dhp97:0":{"pli":"Sāriputtattheravatthu ","html":"<article id='dhp97'><h2 class='sutta-title'>{}</h2>"},"dhp97:1":{"pli":"Assaddho akataññū ca, ","eng":"Lacking faith, a house-breaker, ","html":"<blockquote class='gatha'><p><span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"dhp97:2":{"pli":"sandhicchedo ca yo naro; ","eng":"one who acknowledges nothing, ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"dhp97:3":{"pli":"Hatāvakāso vantāso, ","eng":"purged of hope, they’ve wasted their chance: ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"dhp97:4":{"pli":"sa ve uttamaporiso. ","eng":"that is indeed the supreme person! ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span></p></blockquote></article>"},"dhp98:0":{"pli":"Khadiravaniyarevatattheravatthu ","html":"<article id='dhp98'><h2 class='sutta-title'>{}</h2>"},"dhp98:1":{"pli":"Gāme vā yadi vāraññe, ","eng":"Whether in village or wilderness, ","html":"<blockquote class='gatha'><p><span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"dhp98:2":{"pli":"Ninne vā yadi vā thale; ","eng":"in a valley or the uplands, ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"dhp98:3":{"pli":"Yattha arahanto viharanti, ","eng":"wherever the perfected ones live ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"dhp98:4":{"pli":"Taṃ bhūmirāmaṇeyyakaṃ. ","eng":"is a delightful place. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span></p></blockquote></article>"},"dhp99:0":{"pli":"Aññataraitthivatthu ","html":"<article id='dhp99'><h2 class='sutta-title'>{}</h2>"},"dhp99:1":{"pli":"Ramaṇīyāni araññāni, ","eng":"Delightful are the wildernesses ","html":"<blockquote class='gatha'><p><span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"dhp99:2":{"pli":"yattha na ramatī jano; ","eng":"where no people delight. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"dhp99:3":{"pli":"Vītarāgā ramissanti, ","eng":"Those free of greed will delight there, ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"dhp99:4":{"pli":"na te kāmagavesino. ","eng":"not those who seek sensual pleasures. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span></p></blockquote>"},"dhp99:5":{"pli":"Arahantavaggo sattamo. ","html":"<p class='endvagga'>{}</p></article></section>"}}}